# Private outbound whitelist extension.
#
# Copy this file to:
#   private/outbound-proxy/whitelist.private.txt
#
# Domains here are merged with infra/outbound-proxy/whitelist.txt at container
# startup. scripts/whitelist-domain.sh writes to the private whitelist by
# default, so this file should contain local/project/personal entries only.
#
# Temporary helper entries use inline metadata and are ignored by runtime
# whitelists after expiry:
#   docs.example.com # sg-expires-at=1780300800 sg-ttl=15d
# TTLs are limited to 365 days. Malformed expiry metadata is rejected.
# Hostnames and IPv4 addresses are supported; IPv6 literals are rejected.

# my-company.example
# internal-tool.example
# docs.example.com
